00149 void EagleDbSqlExpression_CompilePlan(EagleDbSqlExpression **expressions, int totalExpressions, int whereClause, EaglePlan *plan)
00150 {
00151     int i, *results, destinationBuffer;
00152     
00153     if(NULL == plan) {
00154         return;

00156     
00157     /* for now we will just assume we don't need more than 10 buffers */
00158     EaglePlan_prepareBuffers(plan, 10);
00159     
00160     /* make sure we don't override buffers that are already assigned by providers */
00161     destinationBuffer = 0;
00162     for(i = 0; i < plan->usedProviders; ++i) {
00163         if(plan->providers[i]->destinationBuffer >= destinationBuffer) {
00164             destinationBuffer = plan->providers[i]->destinationBuffer + 1;
00165         }
00166         
00167         /* each provider will go into a page, sync their types */
00168         plan->bufferTypes[plan->providers[i]->destinationBuffer] = plan->providers[i]->provider->type;
00169     }
00170     
00171     /* prepare result providers */
00172     plan->resultFields = totalExpressions;
00173     plan->result = (EaglePageProvider**) EagleMemory_MultiAllocate("EagleDbSqlExpression_CompilePlan.1", sizeof(EaglePageProvider*), plan->resultFields);
00174     
00175     /* compile expressions */
00176     results = (int*) EagleMemory_MultiAllocate("EagleDbSqlExpression_CompilePlan.2", sizeof(int), totalExpressions);
00177     for(i = 0; i < totalExpressions; ++i) {
00178         char *desc;
00179         EaglePageProvider *provider;
00180         
00181         results[i] = EagleDbSqlExpression_CompilePlanIntoBuffer_(expressions[i], &destinationBuffer, plan);
00182         
00183         if(EagleTrue == EaglePlan_isError(plan)) {
00184             EagleMemory_Free(results);
00185             return;
00186         }
00187         
00188         /*
00189          since we don't know the type of result providers until after we evaluate the expression we can now setup the
00190          result provider now

00192         desc = EagleDbSqlExpression_toString(expressions[i]);
00193         provider = EaglePageProvider_CreateFromStream(plan->bufferTypes[results[i]], plan->pageSize, desc);
00194         plan->result[i] = provider;
00195         EaglePlan_addFreeObject(plan, provider, (void(*)(void*)) EaglePageProvider_Delete);
00196         EagleMemory_Free(desc);
00197     }
00198     
00199     /* if there is a WHERE clause expression only send those records */
00200     for(i = 0; i < totalExpressions; ++i) {
00201         EaglePlanOperation *epo;
00202         char msg[1024];
00203         
00204         if(i != whereClause) {
00205             if(whereClause >= 0) {
00206                 /* send some result data to the provider */
00207                 char *t1, *t2, *t3;
00208                 
00209                 t1 = EagleDataType_typeToName(plan->bufferTypes[results[whereClause]]);
00210                 t2 = EagleDataType_typeToName(plan->bufferTypes[results[i]]);

00212                 
00213                 sprintf(msg, "WHERE <%d> (%s), send <%d> (%s) to provider <%d> (%s)", results[whereClause], t1, results[i], t2, i, t3);

00215                 EaglePlan_addOperation(plan, epo);
00216                 EaglePlan_addFreeObject(plan, epo, (void(*)(void*)) EaglePlanOperation_Delete);
00217                 
00218                 EagleMemory_Free(t1);
00219                 EagleMemory_Free(t2);
00220                 EagleMemory_Free(t3);
00221             }

00223                 char *t1, *t2;
00224                 
00225                 t1 = EagleDataType_typeToName(plan->bufferTypes[results[i]]);
00226                 t2 = EagleDataType_typeToName(plan->result[i]->type);
00227                 
00228                 /* send all the result data to the provider */
00229                 sprintf(msg, "ALL <%d> (%s) to provider <%d> (%s)", results[i], t1, i, t2);
